Crow, bakasana, oh how I love thee....
I used to be so worried about controlling everything, afraid of failing, and falling on my face, figuratively and literally.  After I held my first crow for 3 deep breaths, I was hooked on flying. I love the feeling of balancing on my hands and being a bit upside down. I’ve let things go, tried new things I never would have prior to learning Crow, and fallen on my face more times than I can count. I’ve received black eyes, TMJ, and the best of all, lessons and humility from my falls.  I’ve learned to always look forward. I’m stronger than I think, I am capable of focusing my mind on something, and the worst thing that can happen on my mat and in my life is that I may fall. That’s ok though, I just get back up and try again.  So, if you struggle with this pose, look forward, pull your belly upward, and fly. Most importantly, if you fall, put a blanket in front of your face and try again!!! @omstarsofficial @yogagivesback #crow #bakasana #yogachallenge #yogaeverydamnday

