River’s just being helpful. You know, putting his iPad on my crash pillow (which I guess I don’t need anymore) and stomping on it. It makes everything more meditative. 
Day 5 of #werkyourintentions is a balance pose, going along with the intention: “I am balanced in mind and body.”
.
.
I just discovered I could finally do #bakasana 6 days ago!  I hadn’t tried it for a few weeks, but I’d been practicing my “spider hands” for #resolutionhandstand2019, and fooling around with compression work more than usual. Last Tuesday I saw someone doing crow pose here on Instagram and thought, “I haven’t tried that in awhile.” So I tried it. And shockingly, I suddenly had control!  Before this, any “balance” I achieved felt accidental. It definitely wasn’t consistent. Now my hands and fingers just instinctively know what to do. It was such a strange and abrupt difference! .
.
What is it that made it finally “click” when it never could before?  Learning inversions and balances is such an interesting process. .
.
